<h1><span>Super Cute Pets!</span></h1>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br /></p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<h3 id="toc5"><span>Meet Lily!</span></h3>
<img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/news-02-2020/lily.png" height="312px" width="280px" alt="lily.png" class="image" /></div>
<p>Lily is plaidypus's dog, and she is a very good girl. Why don't you tell us about her, plaid?</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Lily likes to stretch out on comfortable things, like blankets and pillows or my spot of the couch so I have to give her attention. However, when she feels like playing, she loves playing this tag-like game where I chase her in circles around the living room or in the yard. She doesn't usually take to dog toys, but loves to gnaw on rawhides and bully sticks.</p>
</blockquote>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span></p>
<h4><span>Do you have a Super Cute Pet?</span></h4>
<p>Send Uncle Nicolini a PM of your pet and a little blurb telling us about them. Just so you know, by doing so you will be releasing that image under CC BY SA 3.0. This isn't a bad thing, so don't worry about it unless you plan on copyrighting said image!</p>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span></p>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span></p>
<hr />
<h1><span>Q&amp;A:</span></h1>
<h2><span>Q: Can I replace a blurb that you wrote for one of my articles with my own? I'm not satisfied with it.</span></h2>
<p>A: Absolutely. You will always have that option at any point.</p>
<h2><span>Q: I noticed an error/typo/incorrect information and wish to correct it. May I?</span></h2>
<p>A: Sure! If the changes are not limited to your own article(s) and/or are substantial changes across multiple entries, you should post in that month's discussion page and then make the changes.</p>
<h2><span>Q: I wrote an article and it seems to have stuck. Can I send a blurb of mine to one of the frequent collaborators?</span></h2>
<p>A: Yup! It's much easier if you come to us about it, and it gives you the control over what you want shown on the news page.</p>
